From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ayyappa Mantri <ayyappa.mantri@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 03 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] identity: Add options field to user show output

The _format_user() function in python-openstackclient 7.4.0 uses a
hardcoded list of columns that does not include the 'options' field.
This means 'openstack user show' does not display user options such as
ignore_password_expiry and ignore_lockout_failure_attempts.

The previous version (5.4.0, used in bullseye) displayed all fields by
iterating user._info.items(). The 7.4.0 refactor to openstacksdk
(commit 680e3e301137, "identity: Migrate 'user' commands to SDK",
Apr 4 2024) introduced the hardcoded column list but omitted 'options'.

Add 'options' to both the columns and column_headers tuples in
_format_user() so that user options are visible in the CLI output.

This is a backport of upstream commit 9bcb1c5c0076 ("Fix missing
'options' field in 'user show' command", May 20 2025). This patch
can be dropped when the package is upversioned to >= 7.5.0.

Signed-off-by: Ayyappa Mantri <ayyappa.mantri@windriver.com>
---
 openstackclient/identity/v3/user.py | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/openstackclient/identity/v3/user.py b/openstackclient/identity/v3/user.py
index 582122f1..c3a4b5e2 100644
--- a/openstackclient/identity/v3/user.py
+++ b/openstackclient/identity/v3/user.py
@@ -39,6 +39,7 @@ def _format_user(user):
         'id',
         'name',
         'description',
+        'options',
         'password_expires_at',
     )
     column_headers = (
@@ -49,6 +50,7 @@ def _format_user(user):
         'id',
         'name',
         'description',
+        'options',
         'password_expires_at',
     )
     return (
--
2.39.2

